text: Keetia bakossiorum is a species of flowering plant in the family Rubiaceae. It is endemic to Cameroon. Its natural habitats are subtropical or tropical moist lowland forests and subtropical or tropical moist montane forests. It is threatened by habitat loss. ==References== ==External links== *World Checklist of Rubiaceae * Cheek. M. 2004. Keetia bakossii. 2006 IUCN Red List of Threatened Species.
